      "message": "I would prefer to not quote source code to back up your claim that something is missing -- everyone interested can simply look it up in the source code. IMO mentioning the affected files should be completely sufficient, so the commit message could be shortened to something like\n\n\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\n\nBubbles manual missing one exit link\n\nbubbles.c defines two exit links (PLA_EXIT and PLA_CANCEL). However, the manual only mentiones the PLA_CANCEL button. Add the missing one.\n\n\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\n\nIn general you shouldn\u0027t be too verbose in commit messages (though I also have a tedency for being pretty verbose), especially don\u0027t state the obvious and don\u0027t repeat things that are easily to be looked up.",
